<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="71" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicName authorityName="X. Hu" authorityYear="2018" class="Liliopsida" family="Zingiberaceae" genus="Hedychium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hedychium viridibracteatum" order="Scitamineae" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="viridibracteatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Hedychium viridibracteatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
X.Hu, sp. nov. is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wall." class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Zingiberaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. villosum var. tenuiflorum" order="Scitamineae" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="variety" species="villosum" variety="tenuiflorum">H. villosum Wall. var. tenuiflorum</taxonomicName>
Voigt ex Baker by having sagittate anther, long filament, relatively thick and small leaves, more than two flower per-bract, but can be easily distinguished from it by its green (vs. brown) shorter bracts (1.3-1.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.4-0.5 cm vs. 2.7-2.9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.1-1.2 cm) and bracteoles (1.0-1.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.3-0.4 cm vs. 2.1-2.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.7-0.75 cm), pure white flowers (vs. white with red stamen), dentate (vs. acute) tips to the lateral staminodes, and the apex of the labellum incised to the middle (vs. deeply divided).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
