<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="73" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="73">The new species is named after its green bracts and pure white flowers which are highly diagnostic.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="73" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="73">This species is currently found on limestone rocks in Guangxi Autonomous Region (Napo, Longzhou and Jingxi Counties) mainly growing under forest at altitudes of 600-800 m.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="73" type="ploidy level analysis">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Ploidy level analysis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="73">
The results (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Histogram of relative DNA content of nuclei isolated from the leaves of the new plant and related Hedychium species. A H. coronarium (control) B H. viridibracteatum C H. villosum var. tenuiflorum D H. villosum var. villosum." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.110.28710.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/239977" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">4</figureCitation>
) show that, when the nuclei of the diploid control (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Histogram of relative DNA content of nuclei isolated from the leaves of the new plant and related Hedychium species. A H. coronarium (control) B H. viridibracteatum C H. villosum var. tenuiflorum D H. villosum var. villosum." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.110.28710.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/239977" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">4A</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Zingiberaceae" genus="Hedychium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hedychium coronarium" order="Scitamineae" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coronarium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Hedychium coronarium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3969/j.issn.1000-3142.2011.03.007" author="Hu, X" journalOrPublisher="Guihaia" pageId="9" pageNumber="78" pagination="175 - 180" refId="B3" refString="Hu, X, Wu, FC, Liu, N, 2011. Cytologic study of Nineteen Hedychium taxa in China. Guihaia 31 (2): 175 - 180, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3969/j.issn.1000-3142.2011.03.007" title="Cytologic study of Nineteen Hedychium taxa in China." url="https://doi.org/10.3969/j.issn.1000-3142.2011.03.007" volume="31" year="2011">Hu et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1508/cytologia.34.213" author="Ramachandran, K" journalOrPublisher="Cytologia" pageId="9" pageNumber="78" pagination="213 - 221" refId="B9" refString="Ramachandran, K, 1969. Chromosome numbers in Zingiberaceae. Cytologia 34 (2): 213 - 221, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1508/cytologia.34.213" title="Chromosome numbers in Zingiberaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.1508/cytologia.34.213" volume="34" year="1969">Ramachandran 1969</bibRefCitation>
) were set to channel 50, the new plant, 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Zingiberaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. viridibracteatum" order="Scitamineae" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="viridibracteatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">H. viridibracteatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
X.Hu (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Histogram of relative DNA content of nuclei isolated from the leaves of the new plant and related Hedychium species. A H. coronarium (control) B H. viridibracteatum C H. villosum var. tenuiflorum D H. villosum var. villosum." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.110.28710.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/239977" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">4B</figureCitation>
) resolved at channel 100. This means that the new plant is a tetraploid which shares the same level of ploidy with 
<taxonomicName authority="Wall." class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Zingiberaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. villosum var. tenuiflorum" order="Scitamineae" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="variety" species="villosum" variety="tenuiflorum">H. villosum Wall. var. tenuiflorum</taxonomicName>
Voigt ex Baker (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Histogram of relative DNA content of nuclei isolated from the leaves of the new plant and related Hedychium species. A H. coronarium (control) B H. viridibracteatum C H. villosum var. tenuiflorum D H. villosum var. villosum." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.110.28710.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/239977" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">4C</figureCitation>
) but differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="var. villosum" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Zingiberaceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. villosum var. villosum" order="Scitamineae" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="variety" species="villosum" variety="villosum">H. villosum var. villosum</taxonomicName>
Wall. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Histogram of relative DNA content of nuclei isolated from the leaves of the new plant and related Hedychium species. A H. coronarium (control) B H. viridibracteatum C H. villosum var. tenuiflorum D H. villosum var. villosum." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.110.28710.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/239977" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">4D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
